						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the <hi rend="italic">mukhamaṇḍapa</hi> of the Sāṁbaśivēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>HEMAḶAMBI.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in the cyclic year Hemaḷaṁbi, Āshāḍha, ba. 7.</p>						

						<p>It states that Tammuḷa paruvatana got on image of Gaṇēśa made by Ka[nu]mala Kommana and granted (to him) some land near Yammanūru. It also refers to the grant of a <hi rend="italic">pamnasa</hi> by the Kaṁsala community.</p>						

						</summary>
